    "summary": "New Money at Pari Passu Priority: The borrower incurs new first lien debt that ranks equally with existing first lien obligations in terms of lien priority and right of payment. Sweeteners for New Money Providers: Higher spread / coupon – the new...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "New Money at Pari Passu Priority: The borrower incurs new first lien debt that ranks equally with existing first lien obligations in terms of lien priority and right of payment. Sweeteners for New Money Providers: Higher spread / coupon – the new debt carries a higher interest rate than the existing first lien debt Upfront fees / OID – original issue discount or upfront fees compensating the new lenders Equity kickers – warrants, conversion rights, or equity co-investment opportunities Tighter covenants – additional protective covenants that benefit only the new tranche Mandatory prepayment priority – first call on excess cash flow or asset sale proceeds Call protection – non-call provisions or make-whole premiums protecting the new lenders’ yield Participation Rights: New money opportunities are sometimes offered to all existing lenders (pro rata), but often in practice the new money is provided by a sub-group that has negotiated the terms with the borrower."
