    "keywords": "",
    "content": "When evaluating any proposed LME from the lender’s perspective: Map the covenant capacity – Identify every basket (debt, investment, lien, restricted payment) and calculate remaining capacity Read the intercreditor agreement – Understand discharge vs. refinancing definitions, release provisions, and amendment mechanics Model the waterfall – Pre-and post-transaction recovery analysis across multiple valuation scenarios Identify sacred rights – Determine what cannot be changed without your consent Assess litigation strength – Evaluate whether the transaction literally complies with the documents vs. whether there are credible breach arguments Calculate your blocking position – Determine whether you hold enough to block key amendments or control enforcement This reference document covers the foundational concepts of LMEs as they apply to a lender-side analysis in a restructuring case competition. The AMC Entertainment case is an ideal study because it involves multiple LME mechanics (drop-down, non-pro-rata exchange, ICA exploitation) and illustrates both the offensive use of these tools by the borrower/cooperating creditors and the defensive responses available to excluded lenders."
