    "content": "Term Definition Ad Hoc Group Informal group of creditors who band together (usually with counsel) to negotiate collectively AOSA All or Substantially All – sacred right provision protecting against release of all/substantially all collateral Blocking Position Holding enough debt to veto Required Lenders amendments (typically >49.9%) Consent Fee Payment to creditors who agree to an amendment or exchange Cooperation Agreement Contract among creditors committing to act collectively Credit Party A borrower or guarantor under a credit agreement DIP Financing Debtor-in-possession financing provided during Chapter 11 Dropdown Transfer of assets from a restricted to an unrestricted subsidiary Exit Consent Amendment to existing instruments obtained as condition of participating in an exchange First-Out / Last-Out Payment waterfall priority within the same lien Incremental Facility Additional debt capacity permitted under a credit agreement Intercreditor Agreement (ICA) Contract governing relative rights of different creditor classes Investment Basket Covenant provision permitting specified investments (including intercompany transfers) Loan-to-Own Strategy of acquiring debt to convert to equity through restructuring Non-Pro-Rata Treatment favoring certain creditors over others within the same class Open Market Purchase Credit agreement provision permitting debt repurchases in open market transactions Pari Passu Equal priority / ranking PIK (Payment-in-Kind) Interest paid by issuing additional debt rather than cash Priming Creating new debt ranking ahead of existing debt Required Lenders Threshold (usually 50.1%) needed to approve amendments Sacred Rights Provisions requiring unanimous or affected-lender consent Super-Priority Debt ranking ahead of all existing secured debt Trapdoor Basket Investment basket permitting indirect transfers through chains of subsidiaries Unrestricted Subsidiary Subsidiary not subject to the credit agreement’s covenants Uptier Transaction elevating certain creditors above others in priority"
