    "summary": "Company: Serta Simmons Bedding, LLC – the largest mattress manufacturer in North America, operating the Serta, Beautyrest, and Simmons brands. Sponsor: Advent International acquired Serta Simmons in a ~$3 billion LBO in 2012. What Went Wrong: -...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Company: Serta Simmons Bedding, LLC – the largest mattress manufacturer in North America, operating the Serta, Beautyrest, and Simmons brands. Sponsor: Advent International acquired Serta Simmons in a ~$3 billion LBO in 2012. What Went Wrong: - Massive disruption from DTC mattress competitors (Casper, Purple, etc.) - Traditional wholesale distribution model under pressure - Significant LBO debt against declining revenue and EBITDA - COVID-19 created an acute liquidity crisis in early 2020 Capital Structure Pre-Transaction (early 2020): Instrument Amount Priority First Lien Term Loan ~$1.95B First lien Second Lien Term Loan ~$450M Second lien Total Funded Debt ~$2.4B ~10x levered"
