    "article": "5. Incora / Wesco Aircraft (2022-2024) – Platinum Equity Contested Priming",
    "section": "",
    "title": "Transaction Mechanics",
    "url": "research/case-studies.html#sec-transaction-mechanics-5",
    "summary": "The Incora LME (executed in 2022) was one of the most aggressive, combining BOTH the J.Crew dropdown playbook AND the Serta uptier playbook: Platinum Equity organized a transaction with select lenders and the sponsor itself. The company dropped down...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "The Incora LME (executed in 2022) was one of the most aggressive, combining BOTH the J.Crew dropdown playbook AND the Serta uptier playbook: Platinum Equity organized a transaction with select lenders and the sponsor itself. The company dropped down collateral – transferred assets to newly created subsidiaries outside the restricted group. New super-priority secured debt was raised at the subsidiary level, secured by the dropped-down assets. Participating creditors received positions in the new priority structure; excluded creditors saw their collateral coverage dramatically reduced. Platinum Equity invested new capital alongside participating lenders, arguing good faith. Unique Features: - The combination of dropdown AND uptier mechanics made it one of the most structurally complex LMEs. - The sponsor’s direct participation gave Platinum additional leverage. - The transaction was executed very quickly, giving excluded lenders minimal time to organize."
