    "summary": "Company: Envision Healthcare Corporation – one of the largest physician services companies in the U.S., staffing 25,000+ clinicians across 780+ facilities. Sponsor: KKR acquired Envision in a $9.4 billion LBO in 2018 – one of the largest healthcare...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Company: Envision Healthcare Corporation – one of the largest physician services companies in the U.S., staffing 25,000+ clinicians across 780+ facilities. Sponsor: KKR acquired Envision in a $9.4 billion LBO in 2018 – one of the largest healthcare LBOs ever. What Went Wrong: - The No Surprises Act (2022): Federal legislation eliminated surprise medical billing, a significant revenue source for out-of-network emergency physicians. - Post-COVID physician labor cost surge - Insurance companies used IDR process to push down reimbursement rates - EBITDA declined from ~$1B to well below $500M, leaving the company 15x+ levered Capital Structure Pre-Restructuring: Instrument Amount (approx.) Priority First Lien Term Loan ~$5.4B First lien secured Second Lien Term Loan ~$1.3B Second lien secured Unsecured Notes ~$600M+ Unsecured Total Funded Debt ~$7.3B+"
