    "summary": "Pre-Bankruptcy LME Attempts (2022-2023): 1. KKR explored dropdown transactions and uptier exchanges. 2. The Ad Hoc First Lien Group organized early and aggressively. 3. The scale ($7.3B+ debt) and regulatory complexity made a purely contractual LME...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Pre-Bankruptcy LME Attempts (2022-2023): 1. KKR explored dropdown transactions and uptier exchanges. 2. The Ad Hoc First Lien Group organized early and aggressively. 3. The scale ($7.3B+ debt) and regulatory complexity made a purely contractual LME difficult. Chapter 11 Filing (May 2023): 4. Envision filed for Chapter 11 in the Southern District of Texas. KKR’s equity was wiped out. 5. First lien lenders proposed debt-for-equity conversion, taking control of the reorganized company. Creditor Group Dynamics: - First Lien Ad Hoc Group: Coordinated push for debt-to-equity conversion and majority ownership. - Second Lien Ad Hoc Group: Fought for recognition that their liens had value. - KKR: Largely sidelined; its $3.5B equity investment was wiped out. - Physician Practice Considerations: Corporate practice of medicine doctrines complicated restructuring."
