    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Modern credit agreements now include specific provisions to prevent Serta-style transactions. These provisions have evolved rapidly since 2020. 2.2.1 Sacred Right Expansion for Lien Priority Provision: Any amendment, waiver, or modification that would subordinate the liens securing the obligations of any lender to any other debt, or that would change the priority of payment of obligations owed to any lender, shall require the consent of each lender directly and adversely affected thereby (i.e., “affected lender” consent, not just majority consent). Sample Drafting Language (Post-2022 Market Standard): No amendment, modification, or waiver shall, without the prior written consent of each Lender directly and adversely affected thereby: (a) subordinate the Liens securing the Obligations to the Liens securing any other Indebtedness, or subject the Liens securing the Obligations to any new or additional Liens (other than Permitted Liens) that are senior to or pari passu with the Liens securing the Obligations; (b) subordinate the Obligations in right of payment to any other Indebtedness; (c) alter the pro rata sharing or pro rata payment provisions of this Agreement in a manner adverse to such Lender (including by authorizing or permitting any \"open market purchase\" or \"Dutch auction\" or similar transaction that does not comply with the pro rata provisions herein); (d) change the payment waterfall in a manner that would reduce the priority of any payment owed to any Lender relative to any other creditor; (e) release all or substantially all of the Collateral or all or substantially all of the Guarantors (other than in connection with a transaction permitted by this Agreement); (f) permit the incurrence of any Indebtedness that is secured on a senior basis to the Obligations without the consent of each Lender affected thereby. Strongest formulation (2024-2025 “belt and suspenders” approach): Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, no amendment, modification, supplement, waiver, or consent shall: (i) have the effect of (A) subordinating, or permitting the subordination of, the Obligations or the Liens securing the Obligations to any other Indebtedness or Liens, whether through an uptier, priming, or similar transaction, (B) allowing any creditor to receive priority in respect of any Collateral distributions over any Lender, or (C) otherwise modifying the relative priorities among the Lenders, in each case, without the written consent of each Lender adversely affected thereby; (ii) for the avoidance of doubt, neither the Required Lenders nor any other group of Lenders (other than all affected Lenders) shall have the right to (A) subordinate the Liens on the Collateral securing any Lender's Obligations to Liens securing any other obligations, (B) subordinate any Lender's Obligations in right of payment to other obligations, or (C) contractually redirect any Lender's right to receive proceeds of Collateral or other amounts to any other creditor,..."
