    "content": "Creditor cooperation agreements (also called “creditor coalition agreements,” “lender cooperation agreements,” or “creditor pacts”) are side agreements among groups of lenders that bind them to act collectively in response to potential LMEs. They are not part of the credit agreement itself but rather private contracts among lenders. These emerged in force starting in 2020 when excluded lender groups in Serta-style transactions discovered that their lack of coordination was exploited by borrowers engaging in “divide and conquer” tactics."
