    "keywords": "",
    "content": "5.2.1 Minimum Participation and Blocking Thresholds SECTION 2. COOPERATION UNDERTAKINGS. 2.1 Minimum Participation. Each Participating Lender agrees that it shall not, directly or indirectly: (a) sell, assign, transfer, participate, or otherwise dispose of any of its Loans or Commitments (\"Covered Holdings\") if, after giving effect to such transfer, the aggregate principal amount of Covered Holdings held by all Participating Lenders would be less than [33.34]% of the total outstanding Loans (the \"Minimum Threshold\"); (b) consent to, approve, or vote in favor of any Proposed Transaction (as defined below) without the prior written approval of Participating Lenders holding not less than [66.67]% of the aggregate Covered Holdings (the \"Required Participating Lender Threshold\"); (c) enter into any agreement with the Borrower or its affiliates regarding any Proposed Transaction without the prior written approval of Participating Lenders holding not less than the Required Participating Lender Threshold. Key calibration: The Minimum Threshold is typically set at a level that ensures the group maintains a blocking position (>33.33% for matters requiring supermajority consent, or >50% for matters requiring majority consent). 5.2.2 Definition of Proposed Transactions 2.2 \"Proposed Transaction\" means any: (a) amendment, modification, supplement, or waiver of the Credit Agreement that would (i) alter the priority of the Liens securing the Obligations, (ii) subordinate the Obligations in right of payment, (iii) release all or substantially all Collateral or Guarantors, or (iv) modify the pro rata sharing or waterfall provisions; (b) exchange offer, tender offer, or open market purchase of Loans; (c) new money financing offered on a non-pro-rata basis to fewer than all Lenders; (d) any transaction that would result in the priming, subordination, or structural subordination of any Participating Lender's Covered Holdings; (e) any liability management exercise, restructuring support agreement, or similar transaction; (f) any consent solicitation related to any of the foregoing. 5.2.3 Restrictions on Side Deals and Individual Settlements 2.3 No Side Deals. Each Participating Lender agrees that: (a) it shall not enter into any bilateral agreement, understanding, or arrangement with the Borrower, any Sponsor, or any other creditor regarding any Proposed Transaction or any restructuring of the Obligations, in each case, without the prior written consent of the Required Participating Lender Threshold; (b) it shall not accept any consideration (whether in the form of fees, consent payments, improved pricing, collateral, or otherwise) in connection with any Proposed Transaction unless such consideration is offered to all Participating Lenders on a pro rata basis; (c) it shall promptly (and in any event within [2] Business Days) notify the Coordination Advisor of any communication, offer, or proposal received from or on behalf of the Borrower or any Sponsor relating to..."
