    "url": "research/countermeasures.html#sec-62-expanded-sacred-rights-post-2020",
    "summary": "The LME wave demonstrated that the traditional sacred rights framework was dangerously inadequate. Borrower-side advisors could restructure the practical priority and recovery expectations of lenders without triggering any sacred right, so long as...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "The LME wave demonstrated that the traditional sacred rights framework was dangerously inadequate. Borrower-side advisors could restructure the practical priority and recovery expectations of lenders without triggering any sacred right, so long as they did not technically reduce principal, extend maturity, or release collateral. Expanded Sacred Rights in Modern Agreements: SECTION [X]. AMENDMENTS AND WAIVERS. (a) No amendment, modification, supplement, or waiver shall, without the written consent of each Lender directly and adversely affected thereby: Traditional Sacred Rights (Retained): (i) reduce the principal amount of any Loan; (ii) extend the final scheduled maturity date of any Loan; (iii) reduce the rate of interest or any fee payable hereunder; (iv) extend the date for payment of interest or fees; (v) release all or substantially all of the Collateral (except as permitted by the Loan Documents); (vi) release all or substantially all of the Guarantors (except as permitted by the Loan Documents); New / Expanded Sacred Rights (Post-2020 Additions): (vii) subordinate the Obligations in right of payment to any other Indebtedness (whether by contract, by amendment to the waterfall provisions, or by any other means); (viii) subordinate the Liens securing the Obligations to any other Liens, or permit the incurrence of Liens on Collateral that rank senior to the Liens securing the Obligations; (ix) modify the pro rata sharing provisions of Section [X] in a manner adverse to any Lender; (x) modify the payment waterfall provisions of Section [X] in a manner that would reduce the relative priority of any Lender vis-a-vis any other creditor; (xi) amend, modify, or waive any provision of this Section [X] (i.e., the amendment provision itself -- the \"anti-amendment amendment\" protection); (xii) permit any exchange, rollover, or conversion of Loans held by fewer than all Lenders into Indebtedness that is senior to, or secured on a priority basis to, the Obligations held by non- participating Lenders; (xiii) modify the definition of \"Required Lenders\" or any other voting threshold; (xiv) modify any \"yank-a-bank\" or mandatory assignment provision in a manner that would allow such provision to be used to eliminate a blocking position with respect to any sacred right; (xv) change the currency in which any payment obligation is denominated; (xvi) amend, modify, or waive the provisions relating to the designation of Unrestricted Subsidiaries or transfers of assets to Unrestricted Subsidiaries [J.Crew blocker protection]."
