    "content": "SECTION [X]. PRO RATA TREATMENT. (a) Each payment (whether of principal, interest, fees, or otherwise) and each reduction of Commitments shall be applied pro rata among the Lenders in accordance with their respective Pro Rata Shares. (b) No Exchange Offer, Dutch Auction, Open Market Purchase, or similar transaction shall be consummated unless: (i) each Lender is given the opportunity to participate on the same terms and conditions (including price, exchange ratio, fees, and any other consideration) as every other Lender; (ii) if the transaction is oversubscribed, participation is allocated pro rata among participating Lenders based on their respective outstanding Loans; (iii) the Borrower has provided not less than [10] Business Days' prior written notice to all Lenders describing the material terms of such transaction. (c) For the avoidance of doubt, no amendment, modification, or waiver of this Section [X] shall be effective without the consent of each Lender directly and adversely affected thereby."
