    "url": "research/countermeasures.html#sec-73-most-favored-nation-mfn-provisions-for-exchange-offers",
    "summary": "SECTION [X]. MOST FAVORED NATION. (a) If the Borrower or any of its Restricted Subsidiaries consummates any Exchange Offer or incurs any Incremental Facility, and any Lender is offered or receives terms that are more favorable in any material...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "SECTION [X]. MOST FAVORED NATION. (a) If the Borrower or any of its Restricted Subsidiaries consummates any Exchange Offer or incurs any Incremental Facility, and any Lender is offered or receives terms that are more favorable in any material respect than the terms available to other Lenders (including with respect to pricing, security, priority, maturity, covenants, or fees), then: (i) all Lenders shall be entitled to receive the benefit of such more favorable terms; or (ii) such transaction shall not be consummated unless all Lenders are offered the opportunity to participate on the same terms. (b) The MFN protection in this Section shall apply to: (i) interest rate and fee differentials; (ii) priority and lien terms; (iii) maturity and amortization terms; (iv) covenant packages (if the new debt has more favorable covenants); (v) call protection and prepayment terms; (vi) any other economic or structural term that is more favorable."
