    "summary": "Anti-stacking provision: For the avoidance of doubt, the Borrower shall not simultaneously rely on more than one Permitted Investment basket for any single Investment. Each Investment (or portion thereof) shall be allocated to a specific Permitted...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Anti-stacking provision: For the avoidance of doubt, the Borrower shall not simultaneously rely on more than one Permitted Investment basket for any single Investment. Each Investment (or portion thereof) shall be allocated to a specific Permitted Investment basket at the time such Investment is made, and such allocation shall be irrevocable. Restricted Investment categories (2024+ standard): Notwithstanding the foregoing, no Investment basket (including the Available Amount basket, the general investment basket, and the ratio-based basket) may be used for: (a) Investments in Unrestricted Subsidiaries involving the transfer of Material Intellectual Property, Material Real Property, or equity interests in Material Subsidiaries; (b) Investments in Unrestricted Subsidiaries in an aggregate amount exceeding the greater of $[X] and [Y]% of Total Assets; (c) Investments in Affiliates of the Sponsor (other than Restricted Subsidiaries) unless on arm's-length terms certified by the Board; (d) Investments the primary purpose of which is to move assets beyond the reach of the Lenders."
