    "content": "A lender can score a credit agreement’s LME vulnerability on a 0-100 scale: Category Weight Scoring Criteria Anti-Priming 30% 0 = no protection; 50 = partial; 100 = comprehensive Anti-Dropdown 20% 0 = no J.Crew blocker; 50 = partial; 100 = comprehensive Anti-Double-Dip 15% 0 = no protection; 50 = basic; 100 = comprehensive Pro-Rata 15% 0 = standard with loopholes; 50 = enhanced; 100 = fully protected Basket Discipline 10% 0 = permissive; 50 = moderate; 100 = tight Sacred Rights Scope 10% 0 = traditional only; 50 = partially expanded; 100 = fully expanded Score Interpretation: - 80-100: Strong protection – limited LME vulnerability - 60-79: Moderate protection – some LME vectors remain open - 40-59: Weak protection – significant LME vulnerability - 0-39: Minimal protection – highly vulnerable to LME exploitation"
