    "summary": "For each major LME defense, the following summarizes the minimum acceptable language: B.1 Minimum Anti-Serta Provision: “No amendment shall subordinate the Liens securing, or the priority of payment of, the Obligations without the consent of each...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "For each major LME defense, the following summarizes the minimum acceptable language: B.1 Minimum Anti-Serta Provision: “No amendment shall subordinate the Liens securing, or the priority of payment of, the Obligations without the consent of each affected Lender.” B.2 Minimum J.Crew Blocker: “No Loan Party shall transfer Material Intellectual Property to any Unrestricted Subsidiary.” B.3 Minimum Anti-Double-Dip: “No Restricted Subsidiary shall incur Indebtedness the proceeds of which are lent to the Borrower or any other Restricted Subsidiary on a secured or priority basis.” B.4 Minimum Pro-Rata Protection: “All exchange offers and similar transactions shall be offered to all Lenders on a pro rata basis.” B.5 Minimum Sacred Right Self-Protection: “This amendment provision shall not itself be amended without the consent of each Lender.”"
