    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Term Definition Affected Lender A lender whose rights would be directly and adversely modified by a proposed amendment Available Amount A cumulative basket that grows with retained earnings and other inputs, used for restricted payments and investments Builder Basket Component of the Available Amount that grows based on consolidated net income over time Cooperation Agreement Private contract among lenders agreeing to coordinate responses to LME proposals Double-Dip Transaction structure giving creditors effectively two claims on the same collateral pool Dropdown Transfer of assets to an unrestricted subsidiary outside the credit agreement’s restricted group Fiduciary Out Provision in a cooperation agreement allowing a lender to deviate from group commitments when required by legal/fiduciary duties LME Liability Management Exercise – out-of-court restructuring exploiting credit document flexibilities MFN Most Favored Nation – provision ensuring all lenders receive the best terms offered to any lender Open Market Purchase (OMP) Purchase of loans on the secondary market, sometimes used to circumvent pro-rata requirements Priming Creating new debt that has priority over existing debt, typically through an uptier transaction Pro-Rata Sharing Requirement that payments, exchanges, and other transactions treat all lenders proportionally Required Lenders Typically lenders holding >50% of outstanding obligations; the standard majority threshold for amendments Sacred Rights Fundamental provisions that cannot be amended without unanimous or affected-lender consent Unrestricted Subsidiary A subsidiary designated as outside the restricted group, not bound by credit agreement covenants Uptier Transaction that elevates certain debt to a senior position relative to existing pari passu debt Yank-a-Bank Provision allowing borrower to replace a non-consenting lender with a new lender willing to consent Note: I was unable to access WebSearch or WebFetch to pull the most current 2025-2026 developments, so this document draws on comprehensive knowledge through mid-2025. Key industry sources you should consult for the latest updates include: LSTA model provisions and market data; Weil Gotshal & Manges LLP restructuring publications; Kirkland & Ellis LLP leveraged finance alerts; Mayer Brown liability management analysis; S&P LCD leveraged commentary; Reorg Research; and Debtwire. For specific AMC documentation analysis, the indenture texts in your /Users/diego/school/binghamton-non-school/BRx/Spring26CaseComp/NewDocsBRX/ directory should be cross-referenced against this framework."
