    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Factor Lower Risk Higher Risk Credit agreement language Express authority for the transaction; defined terms support the structure Reliance on ambiguous provisions; undefined “open market purchase” exception Participation breadth All lenders offered participation pro rata Select group invited; others excluded Sacred rights Transaction does not implicate sacred rights Transaction effectively modifies payment priority or releases collateral Business purpose Clear operational need (liquidity, maturity extension) Primary purpose is priority improvement for participating lenders Bankruptcy proximity Company has adequate liquidity runway post-transaction Company likely to file within 2 years Intercreditor complexity Single credit agreement; no intercreditor issues Multiple debt tranches with different documents and ICAs Governing law / Serta blockers Credit agreement includes Serta blocker or explicitly permits Legacy agreement without Serta blocker; “open market purchase” reliance Collateral treatment Collateral remains with existing lender group Substantial assets transferred to unrestricted subsidiary Information asymmetry Transparent process; excluded lenders have same information Participating lenders received MNPI; secretive process Excluded lender sophistication Small, dispersed excluded group Large, concentrated group of sophisticated lenders"
