    "summary": "Lead with the business case, not legal threats. Open with: “We believe in the long-term viability of AMC’s business. We are prepared to provide the capital and runway needed to capitalize on the box office recovery.” Present a comprehensive...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "Lead with the business case, not legal threats. Open with: “We believe in the long-term viability of AMC’s business. We are prepared to provide the capital and runway needed to capitalize on the box office recovery.” Present a comprehensive solution, not demands. Show a fully-modeled proposal with pro forma balance sheet, liquidity runway, and debt service coverage. Make the “no deal” scenario clear but not threatening. Include a comparison: “Under the status quo, the company faces $X billion maturity wall with only $Y million liquidity. Our proposal extends maturities and injects $Z million.” Offer management a personal stake. MIP, employment agreements, severance protections convert management from adversary to aligned partner. Create time pressure without ultimatums. “Our commitment to provide new money is available for [X weeks]” – preserves dignity while creating urgency."
