    "summary": "For a lender considering an LME: - The Security Agent cannot independently block a transaction — it follows ICA instructions. - The Instructing Group threshold determines who controls enforcement. Capturing this majority is critical. - The Security...",
    "keywords": "",
    "content": "For a lender considering an LME: - The Security Agent cannot independently block a transaction — it follows ICA instructions. - The Instructing Group threshold determines who controls enforcement. Capturing this majority is critical. - The Security Agent’s ministerial role means it will execute whatever the Instructing Group directs, including releasing collateral, consenting to amendments, or enforcing — making the ICA the true battleground document. - Any creditor-on-creditor violence must navigate the ICA’s consent thresholds, not just the indenture’s."
