    "content": "The Intercompany Agreements create a bilateral web of obligations that cannot be easily unwound. The IP License Agreement is particularly important — AMC’s US operations depend on the AMC brand, which is now owned by Muvico. In a restructuring, Muvico creditors could theoretically threaten to terminate the IP license if AMC defaults on its obligations — a powerful negotiating lever. The prohibition on designating Muvico entities as “restricted subsidiaries” under other debt documents prevents AMC from using external debt covenants to constrain Muvico operations. The UK Holdco intercompany loan gives Muvico creditors a $200M claim on UK Holdco + a pledge on all AMC UK stock — creating cross-entity leverage that Muvico creditors can use in multi-party negotiations."
